task.summary: Small changes around JSON management (there's still something wrong with the code though).
Fixed deleteRoughly method that failed with deleteAll unit test code.
TimedDataWrapper: Fixed a but in getting numbers in the JSON's Map/Object that were Integer instead of String or Long.

We can now fetch a precise event.
Since it is now possible to modify and delete a precise event it's relevant to get a precise event.
Refactoring TimeSerie.get in getData to keep the APIs similar.
Added RegistryNode::copyTo and RegistryNode::moveTo methods to allow to move registry nodes. The registry system is not built to make this operation easy. It should be used only in some rare cases.
We can now hide children nodes starting with a dot (UNIX-style hiding).

DbFile: rewriting over bigger file + append + OK status
- If we rewrite a file on top of a bigger file, it kept the size of the bigger file. Which is very unfortunate especially for cache files. This is now fixed. - We now handle appending in an easy way. - OK status: set when the file is closed, unset when it is opened for writing. This should fix some issues we've add with some cache data written in half.
TTL code was in fact working fine.

Few changes in the deletion code.
Not much to change, everything is pretty much working well.
Forgot to commit this very small changes to the API.
